Eight out of 10 celebrities in South Africa either have a BMW or a Mercedes-Benz behind their garage doors and that isn t surprising at all. The choice to either buy a BMW M3 or a Mercedes AMG C63 remains tough for many car lovers. Just recently, Thato Sikwane, known as DJ Fresh, took to Instagram to showcase his four-pipe Mercedes-AMG C63 S Coupe. . As new as it is in the market, we thought of detailing why it makes it a beast in its crowd oh and the hefty price tag it carries. The C63 S Coupe has been around SA for less than a year now. It features a similar 4.0-litre turbocharged V8 which powers the Mercedes-AMG GT sports car. Its power is rated at 375 kW (56 kW more than its close rival, the BMW M4) and 700 Nm of torque. All that power is sent to the rear wheels through a 7-speed automatic transmission It takes the Mercedes-AMG C63 S Coupe just 3.9 seconds to hurdle from a stop to 100km/h. That&#8217;s 0.2 seconds faster than the BMW M4. Notable features DISTRONIC PLUS adaptive cruise control RACE driving mode for track-specific dynamics. The AMG C63 Coupe is fitted with a sports exhaust system as standard with an exhaust flap to control and vary the sound of the V8 engine depending on the driving mode. The competition includes the Audi RS5 and the BMW M4. . Mercedes-AMG only wants R 1 382 000 before it will hand you one of these. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.